Financial News Sentiment Analysis Natural Language Processing with Deep Learning
Summer 2020
Project URL: https://github.com/notlongp/financial-news-sentiment
Applied Pythons TextBlob and vaderSentiment to perform text polarity analysis, and used clustering algorithms (K-Means
Clustering and Natural Break Optimization) to categorize positive, neutral, and negative articles.
Tokenized and vectorized training data using scikit-learn and nltk, and trained an Artificial Neural Network (with 75%
accuracy) using keras to predict the articles sentiments.
Tokenized and pad sequenced training data using keras, embedded Googles Word2Vec model using gensim, and trained a
Convolutional Neural Network (with 81% accuracy) using keras to predict articles sentiments.
Data was scraped from CNBCs, Reuterss, and the Guardians official websites using Pythons requests and BeautifulSoup.
